Combine orange juice, chili sauce, soy sauce, oil, sugar, orange peel, garlic, salt and hot pepper sauce. Place beef steak in a plastic bag; add marinade, turning to coat. Place orange slices on top of steak. Close bag securely and marinate in the refrigerator for 3 hours (or overnight, if desired), turning occasionally. Pour off marinade and orange slices; discard. Place steak on grid over medium coals.** Grill 10 to 14 minutes, turning once. Prepare fruit salsa. Carve steak into thin slices. Serve steak with salsa. Garnish with orange wedges and cilantro. To make Fresh Fruit Salsa: Combine pineapple, mango, papaya, apple, red and green pepper, vinegar, cilantro sugar and red pepper (May be prepared in advance if desired.) Yield: About 2 1/2 cups